      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm looking at my mortgage statement from wells fargo and its kinda confusing. i have a 30 year fixed at 6.5% and my monthly p&i is like $2100. i was wondering can u explain how much of that is actually hitting the principal vs the interest? like if i look at year 5 vs year 25, how much of my money is just going to interest?",
